{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddca297a9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1831w"},"text":"§ 1831w.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Safety and soundness firewalls applicable to financial subsidiaries of banks","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddca297aa-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" In general","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"An insured State bank may control or hold an interest in a subsidiary that engages in activities as principal that would only be permissible for a national bank to conduct through a financial subsidiary if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca297ab-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the State bank and each insured depository institution affiliate of the State bank are well capitalized (after the capital deduction required by paragraph (2));","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca297ac-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the State bank complies with the capital deduction and financial statement disclosure requirements in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s24a/c"},"text":"section 24a(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca297ad-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the State bank complies with the financial and operational safeguards required by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s24a/d"},"text":"section 24a(d) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca297ae-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the State bank complies with the amendments to sections 23A and 23B of the Federal Reserve Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s371c"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 371c","children":[],"tail":" and 371c–1] made by section 121(b) of the Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddca297af-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Preservation of existing subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding subsection (a), an insured State bank may retain control of a subsidiary, or retain an interest in a subsidiary, that the State bank lawfully controlled or acquired before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-12"},"text":"November 12, 1999","children":[],"tail":", and conduct through such subsidiary any activities lawfully conducted in such subsidiary as of such date."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddca297b0-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of this section, the following definitions shall apply:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca297b1-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Subsidiary","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “subsidiary” means any company that is a subsidiary (as defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1813/w/4"},"text":"section 1813(w)(4) of this title","children":[],"tail":") of 1 or more insured banks."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca297b2-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Financial subsidiary","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The term “financial subsidiary” has the meaning given the term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s24a/g"},"text":"section 24a(g) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"iddca297b3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Preservation of authority","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca297b4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" This chapter","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No provision of this section shall be construed as superseding the authority of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation to review subsidiary activities under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1831a"},"text":"section 1831a of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"iddca297b5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1831w/d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Federal Reserve Act","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"No provision of this section shall be construed as affecting the applicability of the 20th undesignated paragraph of section 9 of the Federal Reserve Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s335"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 335","children":[],"tail":"]."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddca297b6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-21/ch967/s2"},"text":"Sept. 21, 1950, ch. 967, § 2","children":[],"tail":"[46], as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/102/tI/s121/d/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–102, title I, § 121(d)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-12"},"text":"Nov. 12, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1380"},"text":"113 Stat. 1380","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddca297b7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddca297b8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddca297b9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 121(b) of the Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act, referred to in subsec. (a)(4), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/102/s121/b"},"text":"section 121(b) of Pub. L. 106–102","children":[],"tail":", title I, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-12"},"text":"Nov. 12, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1378"},"text":"113 Stat. 1378","children":[],"tail":", which amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s371c"},"text":"section 371c of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddca297ba-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"iddca297bb-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective 120 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-12"},"text":"Nov. 12, 1999","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/102/s161"},"text":"section 161 of Pub. L. 106–102","children":[],"tail":", set out as an Effective Date of 1999 Amendment note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s24"},"text":"sectio